enhanced_by.method_name: predicatedSortedMap(SortedMap<K, V>, Predicate<? super K>, Predicate<? super V>)
enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve creating a new PredicatedSortedMap instance with a given SortedMap and predicates.
headMap relies on the getSortedMap method to retrieve the underlying SortedMap for operations.
The validate method ensures that keys and values meet the predicates before any map operations, which is crucial for the integrity of the headMap operation.
Adding elements to the map via put method should be tested before invoking headMap to ensure the map state is correctly set up.
